COUNCIL: Wellington City Council
FIELD:   Description 1
-  'Statement of service provision: Measurement and reporting of Wellington City Council Group greenhouse gas emissions. The Council has chosen to include a measure of the quantity of greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions from the Council and Group in its performance information. This includes emissions generated directly by the Group itself, as well as indirect emissions related to the products and services used by the Council and Group. We consider this material performance information because the Council has declared a climate emergency and because of the public interest in climate change related information.In measuring its scope 3 GHG emissions, the Council has applied spend-based emissions factors to estimate the GHG emissions associated with certain goods and services, including capital goods, purchased by the Council in the 2025 and 2024 performance years.Our audit testing identified several issues in the application of these spend-based factors, and the Council has determined that further work is required to strengthen the methodologies and assumptions around how supplier spend is categorised and the emissions factors are applied, as explained on page 54 of Volume 1 of the annual report.As a result, our work over the accuracy and completeness of Group’s scope 3 emissions was limited and there were no practicable audit procedures we could apply to obtain assurance over the reported results for 2025 and 2024 for the performance measure described above. Without further modifying our opinion, we also draw attention to the inherent uncertainty disclosure in Volume 1, page 198 of the annual report, which outlines the inherent uncertainty in the reported GHG emissions. Quantifying GHG emissions is subject to inherent uncertainty because the scientific knowledge and methodologies to determine the emissions factors and processes to calculate or estimate quantities of GHG sources are still evolving, as are GHG reporting and assurance standards'
+  'Statement of service provision: Measurement and reporting of Wellington City Council Group greenhouse gas emissions. The Council has chosen to include a measure of the quantity of greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions from the Council and Group in its performance information. This includes emissions generated directly by the Group itself, as well as indirect emissions related to the products and services used by the Council and Group. We consider this material performance information because the Council has declared a climate emergency and because of the public interest in climate change related information.In measuring its scope 3 GHG emissions, the Council has applied spend-based emissions factors to estimate the GHG emissions associated with certain goods and services, including capital goods, purchased by the Council in the 2025 and 2024 performance years.Our audit testing identified several issues in the application of these spend-based factors, and the Council has determined that further work is required to strengthen the methodologies and assumptions around how supplier spend is categorised and the emissions factors are applied, as explained on page 52 of Volume 1 of the annual report.As a result, our work over the accuracy and completeness of Group’s scope 3 emissions was limited and there were no practicable audit procedures we could apply to obtain assurance over the reported results for 2025 and 2024 for the performance measure described above. Without further modifying our opinion, we also draw attention to the inherent uncertainty disclosure in Volume 1, page 180 of the annual report, which outlines the inherent uncertainty in reporting GHG emissions. Quantifying GHG emissions is subject to inherent uncertainty because the scientific knowledge and methodologies to determine the emissions factors and processes to calculate or estimate quantities of GHG sources are still evolving, as are GHG reporting and assurance standards.'

